00:00:07.724 --> 00:00:15.051
Today we will make missi puri.
It is very pleasing in taste and can be consumed for up to 2 days.

00:00:15.265 --> 00:00:20.252
Let’s see what all ingredients are required for making missi puri.

00:00:21.611 --> 00:00:24.373
Wheat flour - 2 cup

00:00:24.851 --> 00:00:28.499
Gram flour - 1 cup Mix gram flour in wheat flour.

00:00:31.814 --> 00:00:33.258
Salt - ½ tsp

00:00:35.601 --> 00:00:37.039
Cumin seeds - ½ tsp

00:00:38.993 --> 00:00:40.596
Oil - 1 tbsp

00:00:47.049 --> 00:00:49.851
Mix all ingredients nicely.

00:01:11.224 --> 00:01:16.100
Take 1 cup water and add little water at a time for kneading flour.

00:01:20.527 --> 00:01:22.981
The dough for making puri is kept bit hard (tight).

00:01:27.700 --> 00:01:34.929
Dough is ready; now keep it aside for 15-20 minutes so that it gets fermented.

00:01:48.462 --> 00:01:50.720
Place oil on flame for heating.

00:01:57.407 --> 00:02:04.110
Knead the dough nicely more making puri puffy.

00:02:09.792 --> 00:02:12.151
Now make small balls from the dough.

00:02:18.724 --> 00:02:23.776
Make small (lemon size) balls.

00:02:24.739 --> 00:02:33.102
Roll the balls like this and like wise make all balls.

00:02:39.262 --> 00:02:51.695
Place some oil on the puri and then roll it.

00:02:56.861 --> 00:03:03.968
Check whether oil is hot or not.

00:03:16.216 --> 00:03:20.186
Place the puri gently in oil.

00:03:27.288 --> 00:03:30.046
Press it gently with ladle

00:03:37.737 --> 00:03:39.832
When it puffs up flip the side

00:03:51.075 --> 00:03:52.394
Place another puri as well.

00:04:11.001 --> 00:04:14.652
Take out the ones fried in basket

00:04:16.990 --> 00:04:19.697
When puri turns little brown take it out.

00:04:55.642 --> 00:04:58.677
Namkeen, crusty missi puri is ready.

00:04:58.844 --> 00:05:05.679
Serve missi puri with aloo tamatar, matar paneer, any other sabzi of your choice, raita or pickle

